            <thetext>Thanks to Jonathan: this works for me: http://tinyurl.com/2wszh3x

The property &quot;focusCellOnMouseMove&quot; has to be true:
table.setFocusCellOnMouseMove(true);

When this property is set to true, in the map &quot;rowinfo&quot; of the row renderer the attribute &quot;focusedRow&quot; is set correctly. Otherwise it is &quot;false&quot; every time.

In my opinion the bug is, that this attribute (&quot;focusedRow&quot;) depends on the property &quot;focusCellOnMouseMove&quot;. There is a property in &quot;qx.ui.table.rowrenderer.Default&quot; called &quot;highlightFocusRow&quot;, which could be used to enable or disable the highlight behaviour. The attribut &quot;focusedRow&quot; should always be correct.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
